# Box MCP Server (cloudflare-box-mcp)

Remote MCP server on Cloudflare Workers that connects Claude Cowork to Box via OAuth 2.0.

## Architecture

- **Runtime**: Cloudflare Workers with Durable Objects (EU jurisdiction)
- **Auth**: OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow with Box as upstream IdP
- **API**: Direct Box REST API calls via lightweight `BoxClient` (no SDK — `box_sdk_gen` is Python-only)
- **Transport**: Streamable HTTP via `OAuthProvider` + `McpAgent`

## File structure

```
src/
  index.ts                 # BoxMcpAgent (DO class) + OAuthProvider (default export)
  oauth-handler.ts         # Hono app: /authorize, /callback against Box OAuth
  workers-oauth-utils.ts   # Generic CSRF, state management, consent dialog
  env.d.ts                 # Env type declarations (secrets, KV, DO bindings)
  lib/
    box-client.ts          # Box REST API client with auto token refresh
    types.ts               # Shared Box types and constants
  tools/                   # One file per tool group, each exports registerXxxTools()
    meta.ts, search.ts, ai.ts, docgen.ts, files.ts, file-transfer.ts,
    folders.ts, metadata.ts, users.ts, groups.ts, collaborations.ts,
    shared-links.ts, web-links.ts, tasks.ts
```

## Conventions

- Tool names: `box_{action}_{resource}` in snake_case
- Every Zod parameter must have `.describe()` — the LLM uses descriptions to fill arguments
- Tools return `{ content: [{ type: "text", text: ... }] }` with JSON.stringify for structured data
- Error messages must be actionable (help the LLM retry or inform the user)
- `registerXxxTools(server, client)` pattern — one function per tool group
- Box API client handles 401 retry with token refresh automatically

